{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"MapLibre Native iOS provides a set of built-in gesture recognizers. You can customize or supplement these gestures according to your use case. You see what gesture recognizers are on your "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNMapView"},{"type":"text","text":" by accessing the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gestureRecognizers"},{"type":"text","text":" property on your map."}]},{"anchor":"Configuring-user-interaction","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Configuring user interaction"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Several properties on an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNMapView"},{"type":"text","text":" provide ways to enable or disable a set of gesture recognizers. Boolean values are set to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" by default."}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNMapView\/zoomEnabled"},{"type":"text","text":" - Allows the user to zoom in or out by pinching two fingers, double-tapping, tapping with two fingers, or double-tapping then dragging vertically. Accepts Boolean values."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNMapView\/scrollEnabled"},{"type":"text","text":" - Allows the user to scroll by dragging or swiping one finger. Accepts Boolean values."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNMapView\/rotateEnabled"},{"type":"text","text":" - Allows the user to rotate by moving two fingers in a circular motion. Accepts Boolean values."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNMapView\/pitchEnabled"},{"type":"text","text":" - Allows the user to tilt the map by vertically dragging two fingers. Accepts Boolean values."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNMapView\/decelerationRate"},{"type":"text","text":" - Determines the rate of deceleration after the user lifts their finger. You can set the value using the  "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNMapViewDecelerationRateNormal"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNMapViewDecelerationRateFast"},{"type":"text","text":", or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNMapViewDecelerationRateImmediate"},{"type":"text","text":" constants."}]}]}]},{"anchor":"Individual-gestures","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Individual gestures"},{"rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Gesture"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Description"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Related Property"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Pinch"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Zooms in or out on the map’s anchor point"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNMapView\/zoomEnabled"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Rotation"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Changes the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNMapView"},{"type":"text","text":" direction based on the user rotating two fingers in a circular motion"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNMapView\/rotateEnabled"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Single tap"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Selects\/deselects the annotation that you tap."}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Double tap"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Zooms in on the map’s anchor point"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNMapView\/zoomEnabled"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Two-finger tap"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Zooms out with the map’s anchor point centered"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNMapView\/zoomEnabled"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Pan"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Scrolls across mapView ("},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"note: if"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNUserTrackingModeFollow"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"is being used, it will be disabled once the user pans"}]},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNMapView\/scrollEnabled"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Two-finger drag"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Adjusts the pitch of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNMapView"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pitchEnabled"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"One-finger zoom"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tap twice; on second tap, hold your finger on the map and pan up to zoom in, or down to zoom out"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNMapView\/zoomEnabled"}]}]]],"type":"table","alignments":["center","unset","unset"],"header":"row"},{"type":"video","metadata":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Rotation with two fingers."}]},"identifier":"rotation.mp4"},{"type":"video","metadata":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"One finger zoom with a double tap."}]},"identifier":"quickzoom.mp4"},{"anchor":"Adding-custom-gesture-recognizers","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Adding custom gesture recognizers"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can add "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uigesturerecognizer"},{"type":"text","text":" to your map programmatically or via storyboard. Adding custom responses to gesture recognizers can enhance your user’s experience, but try to use standard gestures where possible."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The gesture recognizers that you add will take priority over the built-in gesture recognizer. You can also set up your own gesture recognizer to work simultaneously with built-in gesture recognizers by using "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uigesturerecognizerdelegate\/1624208-gesturerecognizer"},{"type":"text","text":", allowing you to enhance already existing gesture recognizers."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can also add gesture recognizers that are only called when the default gesture recognizer fails (and vice versa), such as when a user taps on a part of the map that is not an annotation. The documentation for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNMapView"},{"type":"text","text":" includes an example of how to create a fallback gesture recognizer."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you would like to disable a specific set of gesture recognizers, such as zoom, you can set the Boolean value for the appropriate property to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":". You can then add your own gesture recognizers to perform those actions."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre-native-for-ios\/gesturerecognizers"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/GestureRecognizers","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Lea